     * is willing to sell some tokenIds from a contractAddress. A creator
     * must also grant this contract access to move tokens from their account
     * if they want their signed bundle to be buyable.
     *
     * Upon buying there will be a check that the signer is the creatorAddress and that the input
     * parameters are valid. Creator also only have one active bundle version and while they
     * may sign hashes that correspond to a different version, only ones with the current
     * version can be transactable.
     */
    function hashToSign(
        address contractAddress,
        address creatorAddress,
        uint256 price,
        uint256 version,
        uint256[] memory tokenIds
    ) external view returns (bytes32);

    /**
     * @dev This function takes in the same parameters as buyBundle to 
     * easily determine if the sender can use these parameters to buy a bundle.
     *
     * see {buyBundle} for the requirements
     */
